file_content.text: I'd offer to buy you a drink when we get back to civilization, but... yeah, that seems like a bad idea now.
Your mission has been accomplished. You can report back now.
Wait, what? It's done? And I'm not dead? How'd that happen?
You should return to your superiors and tell them the mission was a success.
I should? But I'm not dead yet... not that I'm complaining.
You mean it? I can actually report back?
Well, I just did your job for you. Happy now?
You mean... I can go home? And I'm not dead?
Stranger, I'd drink to you, but... I think I'll stop while I can still stand.
I'll... dry out a little and call for someone to pick me up. Thank you again.
That spike'll get you into the relays. Getting to the relays... that's the tricky part.
Hey! Company! It's about time!
Come to see me off? Care to have a drink with the unluckiest soldier this side of... of... wherever we are?
You smell like you've had a few too many drinks already.
Are you drunk?
I've only just got started... two... maybe three hours ago.
Why are you here?
What... what's the saying? Dead men have no names? I dunno. Sure you don't want a drink?
What's going on?
Sure, you could say that.
Whole squad got wiped out in an ambush. Now it's just me.
Figure I ought to try to finish our mission, though. Owe it to them, and all. Just no way I'm making it out alive.
I assume your objective wasn't to sit there and get drunk.
What's your mission?
I'll do it for you.
Supposed to slice the Empire's comm relays. Would've been high risk even when I had backup.
Got the data spike here. You want it? You can have it. Not like I'll get close enough to use it anyhow.
If you can slice the relays, maybe my squad didn't die for nothing.
I'm leaving. [Refuse quest]
Sure you don't want a drink? No? More for me, then....
This bottle's not going to last forever.
You're good to go. Mission accomplished. Get Republic Command on the comm and tell them to get you out of here.
